-- Credem plans to tap new longer-term ECB funds for around 700 mln eur
-- By Gianluca Semeraro
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 05:34AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Aug 8 (Reuters) - Italian mid-sized lender Credito Emiliano <EMBI.MI> expects to request around 700 million euros in new longer-term funds the European Central Bank will provide euro zone lenders starting from September in a bid to spur funding to companies.

